<span key="e6ba83b35b6040c5a489cc32f7fa96a6"><span offset-key="e6ba83b35b6040c5a489cc32f7fa96a6:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

## 

<span key="4e57756f78a74c2a9c9780e1b95c0de5"><span offset-key="4e57756f78a74c2a9c9780e1b95c0de5:0">For the most part in my work, I work with various web frameworks, so I will dwell on them in more detail.</span></span>

<span key="b089c65847f74f7c81be73b25bdc9a1d">**Django**<span offset-key="b089c65847f74f7c81be73b25bdc9a1d:1"> is the most famous Python framework. It has many built-in features: Django ORM, support for many DBMS (SQLite, MySQL, Postgresql), built-in templating engine, built-in admin panel, forms, and this is just the bare minimum.1</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="96efcabce52644628765c6dd610c000c"></span>

<span key="9feb4f6fc5a442d79ef4f6ed830099e5"><span offset-key="9feb4f6fc5a442d79ef4f6ed830099e5:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="fc1e12f75ed443ecaf15a1b5fea7234a"></span>

<span key="9f2c681bb7a14853a97ab61f40e53327"><span offset-key="9f2c681bb7a14853a97ab61f40e53327:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="66399dbec77e496a89b84b2c2e5b062a"></span>

<span key="103ac5b461204e76a8b5cd3458fc8afb"><span offset-key="103ac5b461204e76a8b5cd3458fc8afb:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="164e1c15e0fc448fabce495886d370af"></span>

<span key="bb246d5d1a45470da37ca23e2fa91f73"><span offset-key="bb246d5d1a45470da37ca23e2fa91f73:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

<span key="ae6bf6bed05a4c85975816162e8217e5"><span offset-key="ae6bf6bed05a4c85975816162e8217e5:0">The framework is often considered overloaded, which is partly true. But if you figure out the optimization, then you can turn off part of the functionality. Very suitable for testing a prototype or releasing an MVC, also very suitable for hackathons.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="6911d70e0aa34d0e857525268e974e7f"></span>

<span key="3821b378a3d546059fa11f5cc758fb1c"><span offset-key="3821b378a3d546059fa11f5cc758fb1c:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="f9bdb0cd52694e37afc67791c19bf748"></span>

<span key="9e898ab238264bc1b4142a91771d00ed"><span offset-key="9e898ab238264bc1b4142a91771d00ed:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="ced8f3c9611c460da16b820a5a535684"></span>

<span key="69cd78efad1c4be491eaee2ff7c5767c"><span offset-key="69cd78efad1c4be491eaee2ff7c5767c:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="f649d09bf35e48aba59227a7e5abc971"></span>

<span key="d3a44f455b924404865911ba7d224274"><span offset-key="d3a44f455b924404865911ba7d224274:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

<span key="c677d3b445454a7085a95d0542cb5479">**Fastapi**<span offset-key="c677d3b445454a7085a95d0542cb5479:1"> is a modern, fast (high performance) web framework for building APIs and HTML templates. It is very fast due to its asynchrony, it supports WebSocket, swagger, and typing out of the box. It also has a lot of additional libraries that will make the job easier. Suitable for heavy-duty projects.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="71291d34487745f08e3e5b7e4653b06a"></span>

<span key="472d6a648d9a4e348b7088f4a9ee9ccf"><span offset-key="472d6a648d9a4e348b7088f4a9ee9ccf:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="950ee6aa427447bda4deb17876c9279a"></span>

<span key="b69bf1802e6e430ba94108ab325c47df"><span offset-key="b69bf1802e6e430ba94108ab325c47df:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="868925f6a5784a0d8d0d3d13e5c26f45"></span>

<span key="55f6c734cd994ca69ab56e2f0bd906d4"><span offset-key="55f6c734cd994ca69ab56e2f0bd906d4:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="75bb1e6496dd420794e35464fdffe9cf"></span>

<span key="edd0dfcc44544678ac1f9ef6e89d1606"><span offset-key="edd0dfcc44544678ac1f9ef6e89d1606:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

<span key="bccd2b469db941bd8b21f6dedbe6d119">**Flask**<span offset-key="bccd2b469db941bd8b21f6dedbe6d119:1"> is a framework for building web applications in the Python programming language using the Werkzeug toolkit as well as the Jinja2 templating engine. The main difference is that most of the features must be installed manually using the package manager.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="63072cad66b040d7a5e044543f7efd52"></span>

<span key="a980b3f1834f4106beb651b359fd5c6f"><span offset-key="a980b3f1834f4106beb651b359fd5c6f:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="7945ae16378149609b1607aeaa67afc8"></span>

<span key="28ba3017d94d4e7a8f8fe3ebce6c362d"><span offset-key="28ba3017d94d4e7a8f8fe3ebce6c362d:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span><span slate-void="true" key="48a188fe639f494a90fec2e416d94a25"></span>

<span key="2c6f6c066205408abde61dde8585e508"><span offset-key="2c6f6c066205408abde61dde8585e508:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

<span key="d8b3634a4b96494bbb43b8b4bebcfcc5"><span offset-key="d8b3634a4b96494bbb43b8b4bebcfcc5:0">Therefore Flask can be more complex than Django due to its large number of dependencies. Suitable for home projects, and rarely found in a Production environment.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="a83bbd5c9d964d2fa4b2797e09fa1ad7"></span>

<span key="4b36464a464b4144ba4b4c83e7055833"><span offset-key="4b36464a464b4144ba4b4c83e7055833:0">If you want something that works faster, but at the same time work with web development, your choice is </span></span><a href="https://hackernoon.com/tagged/golang?ref=hackernoon.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="502d7dd6bdc34302a643e1127e9bc4bd" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-90578_259-90579-237__"><span data-key="3bbc7470ef894d80b5524876fce5b1a8"><strong>Go (Golang)</strong></span></span></a><span key="d450c5d727b94726a09ce43a3e8769b8"><span offset-key="d450c5d727b94726a09ce43a3e8769b8:0">. An excellent and in-demand language with many different libraries, but it seemed to me too much geared towards web development. The well-known Docker and K8s are written on it. You can get acquainted with the concept of channels, although I first met it in another Python interpreter - Stackless Python.</span></span><span slate-void="true" key="d1be248efa0843f4adb462e5d249c631"></span>

For the most part in my work, I work with various web frameworks, so I will dwell on them in more detail.
